description:
If you want to further support the work I am doing, you can now leave a small donation here: https://buymeacoffee.com/factspark

Separating the continents of Europe and Asia, the roughly 1000 kilometer long Caucasian mountains are forming a massive natural barrier between the Black and Caspian Sea. With its steep topography, raging rivers and thousands of years of history and culture, it holds many interesting geography stories, which we are exploring in this video.

0:48 Physical Geography
4:48 Diversity of the Caucasus
7:12 Peculiarities of the Caucasus
